		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">gamax92 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Your forgetting about making the emulator improve the sound of the games. like instead of the choppy decent of a sound, how about a smooth decent of a sound.</div>
<br />That's entirely doable even on the Famicom hardware. Make a mapper that plays MP3 out the expansion audio pins, then mapper hack your games to use OCRemix music. A lot of early PC Engine CD and Sega CD games were ports from cartridge that did almost exactly this.

		

